==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pianoforte
<hw>Pi*an"o*for`te</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>piano</ets> soft (fr.
L. <ets>planus</ets> even, smooth; see <er>Plain</er>, <pos>a.</pos>) +
It. <ets>forte</ets> strong, fr. L. <ets>fortis</ets> (see
<er>Fort</er>).]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A well-known musical
instrument somewhat resembling the harpsichord, and consisting of a
series of wires of graduated length, thickness, and tension, struck by
hammers moved by keys.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dumb piano</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Digitorium</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Grand piano</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Grand</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Square piano</b></col>, <cd>one with a horizontal frame and an
oblong case.</cd> -- <col><b>Upright piano</b></col>, <cd>one with an
upright frame and vertical wires.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

